==English==

===Noun===
'''field hockey'''

# A form of [[hockey]] played on a grassed [[pitch]] with a hard rubber ball instead of a [[puck]].

====Translations====
* Italian: {{t-|it|hockey su prato|m}}
* Russian: {{t|ru|хоккей на траве|m|tr=xokkéj na travé}}

====Usage notes====
In parts of the world where field hockey is more prominent than [[ice hockey]] it is generally referred to simply as {{term|hockey}}. This is equally true of ice hockey.

